WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.410 --> 00:00:05.160
Known as the idyllic holiday destination,
sunny Hawaii has something for everyone-

00:00:05.160 --> 00:00:10.250
from beautiful beaches, a great culture and
stunning seaside accommodation, guests are

00:00:10.250 --> 00:00:12.839
guaranteed the ultimate getaway.

00:00:12.839 --> 00:00:18.520
HotelsCombined, the world leader in hotel
price comparison presents Hawaii’s Top 10

00:00:18.520 --> 00:00:19.520
Hotels.

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:23.929
Nestled on the coast of Hawaii's "Garden Island"
is the St Regis Princeville.

00:00:23.929 --> 00:00:29.410
With access to beach, pool, spa and golf course,
it's the ultimate place to wind down and forget

00:00:29.410 --> 00:00:33.230
about your stresses.

00:00:33.230 --> 00:00:38.620
Stay in a two-storeyed villa at the Four Seasons
Hualalai for one of Hawaii's most romantic

00:00:38.620 --> 00:00:39.739
escapes.

00:00:39.739 --> 00:00:44.899
With couples spa packages, beach front dining
and water activities to enjoy together, you'll

00:00:44.899 --> 00:00:50.230
quickly forget about everyone and anything
else.

00:00:50.230 --> 00:00:55.239
For those looking for more of a cultural holiday,
the Moana Surfrider on Waikiki Beach, offers

00:00:55.239 --> 00:00:59.500
daily historical tours of Moana as well ukulele
lessons.

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:05.160
Being home to Waikiki’s first and only beachfront
spa makes it worth the visit too.

00:01:05.160 --> 00:01:10.410
With its own white-sand beach, Honolulu's
Kahala Hotel offers a slice of tranquillity

00:01:10.410 --> 00:01:13.760
just 10 minutes away from the bustle of the
town centre.

00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:18.680
Known for its grace and sheer beauty, the
resort is often visited by presidents and

00:01:18.680 --> 00:01:23.140
royalty.

00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:27.390
The Resort Lodge at Koele is the place to
stay for adventurous types.

00:01:27.390 --> 00:01:32.850
With onsite horse riding, archery and golf
as well as nearby 4x4 excursions, hiking trails

00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:39.070
and bicycle routes, there's no excuse not
to get active.

00:01:39.070 --> 00:01:43.060
Five-star Halekulani is one of the most sublime
resorts in Hawaii.

00:01:43.060 --> 00:01:48.500
A favoured option for honeymooners, the beachside
hotel enjoys unobstructed views of the famous

00:01:48.500 --> 00:01:53.090
Diamond Head volcanic crater.

00:01:53.090 --> 00:01:56.710
The Four Seasons resort is the largest hotel
complex in Maui.

00:01:56.710 --> 00:02:01.670
Flanked by the beautiful Hawaiian seas and
the imposing Haleakala mountain, it's the

00:02:01.670 --> 00:02:05.670
perfect place to admire the island's beauty.

00:02:05.670 --> 00:02:11.330
Lounging and lazing is the name of the game
at Kapalua Ritz-Carlton too.

00:02:11.330 --> 00:02:16.450
Top up your tan by the 10,000 square-foot
pool, which is spread over three levels, and

00:02:16.450 --> 00:02:24.150
with twice that space devoted to sun chairs
and shaded gazebos, there's always space available.

00:02:24.150 --> 00:02:27.750
Beachside Grand Wailea makes best use of its
seaside position.

00:02:27.750 --> 00:02:32.460
Start the day with beach yoga, then sign up
for a SCUBA programme or go your own way with

00:02:32.460 --> 00:02:34.340
the beach club's snorkel gear.

00:02:34.340 --> 00:02:41.170
Guided kayak tours along South Maui’s pristine
coastline are also available.

00:02:41.170 --> 00:02:46.430
For the ultimate Hawaiian experience, a stay
at the Hilton Waikoloa offers sunset dining,

00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:50.040
dolphin encounters and traditional Hawaiian
luaus.

00:02:50.040 --> 00:02:55.150
Canal boats are also used to get around the
62-acre oceanfront resort, to visit one of

00:02:55.150 --> 00:03:06.459
the three pools, the onsite spa or one of
the 14 dining options.

